# Update README with code changes

When you modify project files (especially `App.js`, `app.json`, `package.json`, or game/reward logic), also update `README.md` in the same task.

## Required updates

Reflect any changes to:

- Features, screens, and user-facing behavior
- Game list, rounds per game (`MAX_ROUNDS`), scoring, stars, high scores
- Rewards: garden coins, badges, unlock conditions, storage keys
- Dependencies, scripts, setup/run instructions
- Project structure and configuration (`app.json`, Expo SDK)

## Guidelines

- Keep README accurate and concise; remove outdated info (e.g. old round counts or missing features).
- Do not skip README updates because the user did not mention it — treat docs as part of the deliverable.
- If a change is trivial (typo in a comment only), README update is optional.
